The Khoisan King of South Africa spoke with eNCA's Khayelihle Khumalo. Courtesy of #DStv403 PRETORIA -  A Khoisan community that's been camped outside the Union Buildings in Pretoria is not going anywhere for now. The Public Works Department has put its eviction plans on hold. READ: Khoisan seek better recognition The group has been on the doorstep of the president's offices for almost two years, seeking to be recognised as the first indigenous nation in South Africa. The Khoisan King of South Africa said the community wants ancestral land to be given to them.